You can use the following JavaScript code to extract data from `localStorage` and `sessionStorage`. 

```javascript
// Get all items from localStorage
function getLocalStorageItems() {
    const storage = window.localStorage;
    for (const key in storage) {
        if (storage.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
            const item = storage.getItem(key);
            console.log(`Key: ${key}, Value: ${item}`);
        }
    }
}

getLocalStorageItems();

// Get all items from sessionStorage
function getSessionStorageItems() {
    const storage = window.sessionStorage;
    for (const key in storage) {
        if (storage.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
            const item = storage.getItem(key);
            console.log(`Key: ${key}, Value: ${item}`);
        }
    }
}

getSessionStorageItems();
```

You can call `getLocalStorageItems()` and `getSessionStorageItems()` functions to log all the items in your browser's local storage and session storage.

Make sure you are running this code in a browser environment. If you're running it in a Node.js environment, you won't have access to the browser's storage objects (`localStorage` and `sessionStorage`).
